The paper deals with the study of linear circuits and their lower bounds, which falls under the category of computational complexity (cs.CC). The use of extremal graph theory suggests a connection to discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The study of the Sierpinski gasket matrix involves fractals and geometric algorithms, which could be categorized under computational geometry (cs.CG). The use of information theory in proving lower bounds suggests a connection to information theory (cs.IT).
